The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Nath upbeat on new SEZ bill

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, March 10: Union commerce minister Kamal Nath today said he would soon present in Parliament the new bill on special economic zones (SEZs) as part of the government?s focus on improving the investment climate in India through a series of legal measures.

 Addressing the inaugural session of the India trade and investment forum on ?The resurgent India: It?s challenges and opportunities? organised by the CII, the Commonwealth Business Council and the department of industrial policy, Nath said the meeting of the commonwealth heads of government had already endorsed a 16-point action programme for governments and businesses to promote investment among member states. These relate to fostering conducive business environments by governments and better corporate governance for companies. 




